```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "sims",
    "output_file": ".out/sims2.out",
    "error_file": ".err/sims2.err",
    "run_time": "3:00:00",
    "mail_type": "END",
    "mail_user": "henrymj@stanford.edu",
    "nodes": 1,
    "mpi_tasks": 24,
    "partition": "russpold,normal",
    "environment": {
      "PYTHONPATH": "",
      "conda_environment": "py3-env"
    },
    "command": "python ../../scripts/simulate_individuals.py --mu_suffix SSRTscale-0_RTscale-0 --abcd_dir /oak/stanford/groups/russpold/users/henrymj/ABCD_simulations/abcd_data --out_dir /oak/stanford/groups/russpold/users/henrymj/ABCD_simulations/simulated_data/individual_data --subjects"
  }
}
```

The script is running on a cluster managed by the **Slurm** workload manager. It defines a job named **sims** that runs for a maximum of **3 hours**. Output and error logs are redirected to the specified files.  The job requests a single node with **24 MPI tasks**.  It runs on the **russpold** and **normal** partitions. The script sets up a Python environment using conda and executes a Python script named **simulate_individuals.py**.  This script is executed multiple times, each time with different subject IDs.
